OL,3,CThe 'money-saving' asylum seeker plan
OL,4,Ccosting taxpayer #46m extra
OL,6,FLarge accommodation sites for asylum
OL,7,Fseekers, like RAF Scampton, were
OL,8,Fsupposed to save the taxpayer money.
OL,10,FThat's what the Government has told us
OL,11,Frepeatedly, pointing out that the
OL,12,Falternative - housing asylum seekers
OL,13,Fin hotels - costs millions of pounds a
OL,14,Fday.
OL,16,FIt was the line the Home Office used
OL,17,Fto quell opposition from local
OL,18,Fcommunities and concerns from refugee
OL,19,Fcharities and human rights groups.
