OL,3,CThe 'money-saving' asylum seeker plan
OL,4,Ccosting taxpayer #46m extra
OL,6,FTime and again it issued a stock
OL,7,Fresponse to questions about how
OL,8,Fmigrants were being housed: "The use
OL,9,Fof hotels to house asylum seekers is
OL,10,Funacceptable - there are currently
OL,11,Fmore than 51,000 asylum seekers in
OL,12,Fhotels costing the UK taxpayer
OL,13,F#6million a day.
OL,15,F"The use of hotels is a temporary
OL,16,Fsolution, and we are working hard with
OL,17,Flocal authorities to find appropriate
OL,18,Faccommodation."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G2/13
