OL,3,CThe 'money-saving' asylum seeker plan
OL,4,Ccosting taxpayer #46m extra
OL,6,FOne of the key reasons is that the
OL,7,FGovernment massively underestimated
OL,8,Fhow much it would cost to get these
OL,9,Fsites up and running.
OL,11,FThe Home Office initially expected to
OL,12,Fspend around #5million to refurbish
OL,13,FRAF Scampton and get it ready for
OL,14,Fasylum seekers to move in. In the end,
OL,15,Fthey spent #27million.
OL,17,FThat means, according to the NAO's
OL,18,Fcalculations, the Scampton plan will
OL,19,Fcost #45million more than hotels.
