OL,3,CThe 'money-saving' asylum seeker plan
OL,4,Ccosting taxpayer #46m extra
OL,6,FThe Government's defence is that using
OL,7,Fhotels to house asylum seekers is
OL,8,F"unacceptable."
OL,10,FA spokesperson for the Home Office
OL,11,Fsaid: "We have always been clear that
OL,12,Fthe use of asylum hotels is
OL,13,Funacceptable, and that's why we acted
OL,14,Fswiftly to reduce the impact on local
OL,15,Fcommunities by moving asylum seekers
OL,16,Fonto barges and former military sites."
