OL,3,CThe 'money-saving' asylum seeker plan
OL,4,Ccosting taxpayer #46m extra
OL,6,FIt's true that "asylum hotels" have
OL,7,Falso faced fierce opposition; that
OL,8,Fthey've lost business because some
OL,9,Fhotels in the town are housing asylum
OL,10,Fseekers.
OL,12,FSo for some, news that the Government
OL,13,Fplans to close its 100th such hotel
OL,14,Fthis week, down from 400 which were in
OL,15,Fuse last October, will be welcome.
OL,17,FBut the Government's outrage that
OL,18,Fasylum seekers were being given four-
OL,19,Fstar hotel accommodation now looks
OL,20,Flike gesture politics.
