OL,3,CThe 'money-saving' asylum seeker plan
OL,4,Ccosting taxpayer #46m extra
OL,6,FThe Home Office's own value assessment
OL,7,Fexcludes "sunk" costs of around #199
OL,8,Fmillion i.e. what's been spent already
OL,9,Fpreparing sites for migrants to move
OL,10,Fin, and thereby concludes they'll be
OL,11,F#153 million cheaper than hotels.
OL,13,FThat's a bit like saying a mortgage is
OL,14,Fcheaper than renting, but not counting
OL,15,Fthe deposit you need to buy a house in
OL,16,Fthe first place.
OL,18,FConsidering it's the taxpayer footing
OL,19,Fthe bill of this "deposit", many might
OL,20,Fnot be as optimistic as the Government.
